paragraphs.text:
%md ## Welcome to the GeoWave KMeans Example (EMR Version). ##### This is a live note - you can run the code yourself. ### Expectation

This example is a subset of the GeoWave Quick Start Guide.
You will configure a GeoWave datastore and ingest GDELT data into it.
You will then run the KMeans analytic against the GDELT data to generate a set of centroids,
exporting the GeoWave results to a CSV file that will be loaded into a Spark dataframe.
The centroids dataframe can then be shown in the table and on the Leaflet map.

### Setup

The only prerequisite to running this example is increasing your shell interpreter's timeout.
Go to the Interpreter page, and scroll down to the 'sh' section. Click on the 'edit' button.

Set the 'shell.command.timeout.millisecs' entry to 600000 (10 minutes).

### Execution

The list of paragraphs below needs to be run sequentially.
Start at the top, and click the play button in each paragraph, waiting for completion.
Each paragraph is labeled and commented so you can tell what's happening. A paragraph will be marked
with a FINISHED indicator next to the play button when it has run without error.

Enjoy!

paragraphs.title: Configure GeoWave Session
paragraphs.text:
%sh
# Use /mnt/tmp folder w/ open permissions
cd /mnt/tmp
wget s3.amazonaws.com/geowave/latest/scripts/emr/quickstart/geowave-env.sh
source geowave-env.sh

geowave config geoserver "$HOSTNAME:8000"

geowave config rmstore gdelt
geowave config addstore gdelt --gwNamespace geowave.gdelt -t hbase --zookeeper $HOSTNAME:2181

geowave config rmindex gdelt-spatial
geowave config addindex -t spatial gdelt-spatial --partitionStrategy round_robin --numPartitions $NUM_PARTITIONS

geowave config rmstore kmeans
geowave config addstore kmeans --gwNamespace geowave.kmeans -t hbase --zookeeper $HOSTNAME:2181

geowave config list

paragraphs.title: Download GDELT Data (One month - 2016/02)
paragraphs.text:
%sh
cd /mnt/tmp
mkdir gdelt
cd gdelt
wget http://data.gdeltproject.org/events/md5sums
for file in `cat md5sums | cut -d' ' -f3 | grep "^201602"` ; \
do wget http://data.gdeltproject.org/events/$file ; done
md5sum -c md5sums 2>&1 | grep "^201602"
cd ..

paragraphs.title: Ingest GDELT into GeoWave datastore
paragraphs.text:
%sh
# Set your shell timeout to 10 min or so
geowave ingest localtogw /mnt/tmp/gdelt gdelt gdelt-spatial -f gdelt --gdelt.cql "BBOX(geometry,0,50,10,60)"

paragraphs.text:
%sh
# clear out old runs
geowave remote clear kmeans

# run kmeans
geowave analytic kmeansspark gdelt kmeans -k 8 --hulls

# check the output
geowave analytic sql "select * from kmeans|kmeans-hulls" --show 8

paragraphs.title: Export KMeans Centroids to CSV
paragraphs.text:
%sh
# Set up the temp folder
cd /mnt/tmp
rm -rf kmeans
mkdir kmeans

# Query kmeans centroids and write to local temp file
geowave analytic sql "select * from kmeans|kmeans-centroids" --csv /mnt/tmp/kmeans

# Move the csv output to hdfs
mv kmeans/part*.csv kmeans-centroids.csv
hdfs dfs -rm /user/zeppelin/kmeans-centroids.csv
hdfs dfs -put kmeans-centroids.csv /user/zeppelin/kmeans-centroids.csv
